tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All laboratory values are within normal limits except for a markedly low HbA1c (2.9%), which may indicate recent hypoglycemia, anemia, or altered red cell turnover. Glucose is at the lower end of normal. Renal function and electrolytes are unremarkable. Correlation with clinical context and possible further evaluation of low HbA1c is recommended.
